caption: Great first experience at Meze. We had reservations to sit outdoors and were a little concerned that it would be cold. The heaters kept us warm so we could enjoy the food and our company. We ordered the mixed plate of meats, and they were cooked very well. The chicken could have been a bit more tender, but overall it was excellent. We also got the halloumi plate and the pesto dressing was amazing. We finished off dinner with both baklava and kunafa. Both were good but the kunafa was amazing. Our server was attentive and the food came out at a good pace. We'd definitely return.

A pretty great place down in Adam's Morgan. The food is very good and unique. I'd specifically recommend the full dip combo.  For this place, it's basically a series of appetizer sized plates that are meant to be shared with a group. If you're looking for a more "full" meal, you may want to get 3-4 plates per person. Most dishes are between 10-15 bucks so it can add up to be a bit more than other places if you're not careful. There are also more conventional entrees.  A word on parking: Parking straight up sucks in this area. There are a few areas, like California Ave, where parking is a bit better but I've driven around for up to 30 minutes trying to find parking. Worst times are the weekends after 8. There is one garage nearby, however it runs up to 20 bucks on weekends. Read the signs carefully.

Anyone can do that, the reason that I order Turkish coffee in a Turkish restaurant!!! is to have handcrafted coffee. Even though I expressed that I am very displeased with the coffee the waiter totally ignored it! Usually when this happens at other restaurants, the manager comes and apologizes or they usually take the coffee out of the bill! None happened! Won't be back to this restaurant. This is now my favorite Turkish restaurant when friends are visiting from out of town and also for after work gatherings. The place is lively and has both indoor and outdoor seating, weather permitting, in the central Adams Morgan stretch on 18th street. It has a good atmosphere and a screen loops pictures of daily life in Turkey over the years. The wait staff is very courteous and attentive and service is efficient. They are always happy to provide suggestions and small plate mezes are the way to go. Their selection of wine and mojitos is (really) extensive.
